## Automated Tests

Postman allows writing JavaScript tests that run after the response.

Example for a GET /books:
```javascript
pm.test('Status code is 200', () => {
  pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});
pm.test('Response is an array', () => {
  pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');
});
```

You can also set environment variables to chain requests (e.g., save created ID for later).
